text:
5.2.3 Medical Leave

In special circumstances of serious illness or a serious accident due to which an employee is incapable of performing duty beyond a period of 10 days, he/she shall be entitled to medical leave which;

a) Shall be on full salary:

b) Shall not exceed 60 days at a stretch: beyond that an employee will be on leave without pay;

c) Shall be admissible on production of medical certificate of such illness or accident issued by an authorized medical officer of a Government hospital;

After prolonged or contagious illness, HR may require a fitness certificate before return to duty. For maternity-related complications, sick leave may supplement maternity leave with medical proof. Frequent or suspicious sick leave patterns may trigger medical verification.

